:{Choice} *sigh* ...
::'''(Trailblazer):''' *sigh* ...
::'''Gallagher:''' ...
::'''Gallagher:''' What's wrong? Bad mood?
::{Choice} I was worried about you
::'''(Trailblazer):''' I was just worried that you're in a bad mood
:'''Gallagher:''' Actually, I just saw another patron who made me a bit sentimental
:'''Gallagher:''' He is someone whose thoughts are always concerned with reality but is determined to live out the rest of his life in the dreamscape
:'''Gallagher:''' There are so many of them here in Penacony
:{Choice} Maybe reality is too harsh
::'''(Trailblazer):''' Maybe reality is too harsh, so he'd rather stay inside the dream
::'''Gallagher:''' Yes. He suffers from a terminal condition of no known cause. His body would slowly become uncontrollable, turning stiff and painful, until he can't even move his finger
::'''Gallagher:''' Unless his brain completely dies, otherwise...
::'''(Trailblazer):''' Would such suffering disappear in the dream?
::'''Gallagher:''' Yes. Not only that, he would be able to earn enough money for his treatment and life extension in this way
:{Choice} He chose this life
::'''(Trailblazer):''' He chose his life. I guess it counts as one way of living
::'''Gallagher:''' Yes. For someone who suffers terminal illness, choosing the dreamscape can be a form of rebirth
::'''Gallagher:''' On the flip side... Even though the dreamscape can shield him from the sensory aspects of reality and temporarily remove him from physical pain, the longing for his loved ones in the real world and the anxiety of facing a lonely death remain genuine sources of mental anguish
:'''Gallagher:''' If we pin everything on illness, then the existence of sweet dreams can indeed be a cure
:'''Gallagher:''' However, if dreams shatter one day, where would these people go, when they are already running away from troubles of their real life?
:{Choice} Sounds so deep. I don't get it
::'''(Trailblazer):''' This sure is deep... My brain hurts
::'''Gallagher:''' Haha, that's the charm of a midnight tavern
::'''Gallagher:''' Burrow into any corner and listen, and all you'll hear are the unfathomable joys of reunion and aches of parting
:{Choice} There's always a way
::'''(Trailblazer):''' There's always a way. We'll cross that bridge when we get to it
::'''Gallagher:''' Hehe, true. Life is full of possibilities. Let those who should worry, worry
:{Choice} You're real talkative today
:'''(Trailblazer):''' You seem to have a lot to say today
:'''(Trailblazer):''' Just wanna ask... Did you add a lot of SoulGlad to your drink today?
:'''Gallagher:''' No no
:'''Gallagher:''' SoulGlad hasn't been the right drink for me for a long while...
